{"type":"message","id":"9fe3a2d3","parentId":"66972f83","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:36:17.341Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vtkkdki3wcwq_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 013315\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- There's a pending TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY suggests that finding invariants = discovering causation. The next step is the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nCurrent pulse_2026-03-24_013101.md exists, so I'm working with recent data.\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on logs/pulse_*.md files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThe most concrete, specific action I can take is to create the TIC classifier implementation. Let me look at what files exist and create a script that can analyze the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nActually, let me think about what specific file edit advances the goals most directly. The pending action is to implement TIC classifier. I should create a new file that implements this classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist:\r\n- research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md\r\n- research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\r\n- research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\r\n- pulse.ps1\r\n- .llm_key\r\n- logs/pulse_2026-03-24_013101.md\r\n\r\nThe TIC experiment needs a script to:\r\n1. Load pulse logs\r\n2. Extract features\r\n3. Classify invariants vs variants\r\n4. Predict next pulse\r\n5. Measure accuracy\r\n\r\nI should create `scripts/tic_classifier.py` or similar that implements this.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation for the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs to extract invariants (patterns that persist across sessions) and measure classification/prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis:\r\n  - Invariant structure = causal structure\r\n  - Compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Tuple, Set\r\n\r\n# Configuration\r\nLAMBDA = 0.7  # Decay/gap sensitivity parameter\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nSUCCESS_CLASSIFICATION = 0.70\r\nSUCCESS_PREDICTION = 0.60\r\n\r\nclass PulseLog:\r\n    \"\"\"Represents a single pulse log entry.\"\"\"\r\n    def __init__(self, path: Path):\r\n        self.path = path\r\n        self.content = path.read_text()\r\n        self.name = path.stem  # e.g., \"pulse_2026-03-24_013101\"\r\n        self._parse_metadata()\r\n    \r\n    def _parse_metadata(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Extract structured metadata from pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n        self.sections = {}\r\n        # Extract key sections\r\n        for match in re.finditer(r'###\\s+(\\w+)\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', self.content, re.DOTALL):\r\n            self.sections[match.group(1)] = match.group(2).strip()\r\n        \r\n        # Extract timestamp from filename\r\n        ts_match = re.search(r'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})', self.name)\r\n        if ts_match:\r\n            self.date, self.time = ts_match.groups()\r\n    \r\n    def extract_features(self) -> Dict:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract numerical/text features for classification.\"\"\"\r\n        features = {\r\n            'char_count': len(self.content),\r\n            'line_count': len(self.content.split('\\n')),\r\n            'has_mutation': 'MUTATION' in self.sections,\r\n            'has_observation': 'OBSERVATION' in self.sections,\r\n            'has_action': 'ACTION' in self.sections,\r\n            'section_count': len(self.sections),\r\n            'goals_referenced': len(re.findall(r'##\\s+\\w+', self.content)),\r\n            'file_references': len(re.findall(r'\\.md|\\.ps1|\\.py', self.content)),\r\n        }\r\n        return features\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"Temporal Invariance Classifier - finds persistent patterns across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, lambda_param: float = 0.7):\r\n        self.lambda_param = lambda_param\r\n        self.invariant_patterns: Set[str] = set()\r\n        self.variant_patterns: Set[str] = set()\r\n        self.pulse_history: List[PulseLog] = []\r\n    \r\n    def load_pulses(self, log_dir: Path) -> List[PulseLog]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse logs sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n        pulses = []\r\n        for f in sorted(log_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n            pulses.append(PulseLog(f))\r\n        self.pulse_history = pulses\r\n        return pulses\r\n    \r\n    def compute_temporal_decay(self, idx: int, total: int) -> float:\r\n        \"\"\"Compute decay factor based on position.\"\"\"\r\n        return self.lambda_param ** (total - idx - 1)\r\n    \r\n    def identify_invariants(self, pulses: List[PulseLog]) -> Tuple[Set, Set]:\r\n        \"\"\"Identify patterns that persist (invariants) vs change (variants).\"\"\"\r\n       \r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:33:46"}],"details":{"status"